; mesh-merge-converge.form — gossip convergence: many paths, one merged value.
;
; THE ASK (federated-slices.form, milestone M2):
;   "three-cell mesh merge: two cells flood a slice-update via mesh-relay (content-address dedup), the
;    third merges both and applies it — assert mesh-merge == local-merge (gossip convergence as a proof)."
;
;   The fear an orchestrator answers with a coordinator: "if deltas arrive in different orders at
;   different cells, the cells will disagree." The body's answer is that the MERGE itself is order-free,
;   so there is nothing to coordinate. A cell that has seen the same set of deltas holds the same slice,
;   no matter which gossip path delivered them. Convergence is a property of the recipe, not of a referee.
;
; THE SHAPE  (runnable: form-stdlib/mesh-merge-converge.fk · proven: tests/mesh-merge-converge-band.fk -> 127)
;
;   This recipe carries NO arithmetic of its own — it composes slice-merge.fk's sm-num / sm-den (the
;   trust-weighted FedAvg + TIES sign-election merge, proven three-way -> 127) and proves ONE thing about
;   them: their value at a coordinate is invariant under reordering of the slice list.
;   1. PERMUTE  mm-perm: a re-cons of the same three cells — no element added or lost, only order changed.
;      The six orderings of {A,B,C} are the six gossip paths the three deltas can arrive by.
;   2. CONVERGED-AT  mm-converged-at?: do two orderings merge to the same value at coordinate j? The WHOLE
;      rational must agree — numerator AND denominator (binary and, nested) — not half of it.
;   3. ORDER-STABLE  mm-order-stable?: a→b→c merges to the same value as c→b→a (the named diagonal, full
;      reverse) and as the other four permutations, at every coordinate. This IS gossip convergence:
;      because slice-merge's merge is a fold of integer add over the slices, it is commutative AND
;      associative, so the merged value is path-independent. mesh-merge == local-merge.
;   4. GONE-PEER LAW  mm-gone-stable?: a weight-0 delta (a faded or departed cell) joins the set without
;      moving the merged value. The safety floor of convergence — a silent peer can neither corrupt the
;      value nor block the field from agreeing.
;
; WHY IT MATTERS:
;   the convergence is integer-exact (slice-merge defers the divide), so every cell agrees on the same
;   NUMBERS, bit-identical three-way (Go=Rust=TS) — a float-averaging PyTorch federation, where order of
;   summation perturbs the low bits, cannot promise this. Eventual consistency without a coordinator,
;   without a clock, without a trusted prover: the merge is the proof.
;
; THE PROVEN VERDICT — tests/mesh-merge-converge-band.fk -> 127, three-way, 0 divergent:
;   A=(w2,[3,-2,5]) B=(w1,[1,4,-5]) C=(w3,[2,-1,-4]); merged coord0 = (13 6), coord1 = (-7 5), coord2 = (-17 4).
;     1   the merge computes the right numerator         (mm-num coord0 == 13)
;     2   the merge computes the right denominator       (mm-den coord0 == 6)
;     4   a→b→c converges with c→b→a (full reverse, all 3 coords)
;     8   order-stable across ALL SIX permutations of {A,B,C}   (the core gossip-convergence claim)
;     16  sign-election survives reordering              (mm-num coord2 == -17, the elected − side, not all-+)
;     32  a gone peer (weight 0) does not move the merge  (merging +gone == merging without, 3 coords)
;     64  the test can DETECT divergence                 (a tampered delta does NOT converge — falsifiable, not vacuous)
;   Falsified live: making the tampered delta identical drops bit 64 -> 63, so the negative claim is real work.
;
; KIN — the body already holds every piece; this proves they converge:
;   slice-merge.fk (sm-num / sm-den — the merge whose convergence this proves; M0 -> 127) ·
;   federated-slices.form (the M0–M5 ladder; this is M2, gossip convergence) · mesh-relay.fk (managed
;   flooding, content-address dedup — the paths whose order this proves does not matter) · cell-sync.fk +
;   merkle.fk (verify-by-re-address — the address is the convergence key) · confidence-weighted-vote.fk
;   (the integer weight-sum spine slice-merge specializes) · trust-decay.fk (the per-peer weight; a
;   gone peer's weight-0 is the grace-band floor) · cell-numerics.form (vector_add/scalar_mul apply the
;   merged delta) · the three-way validate.sh (no trusted prover — what survives the agreement).
;
; LINEAGE:
;   federated-slices.form · slice-merge.fk · mesh-relay.fk + mesh-health.fk + mesh-gradient.fk (the mesh
;   ring) · the gossip / decentralized-SGD literature (managed-flooding + pairwise merge = gossip without
;   ever calling it that) · CRDT eventual-consistency (a commutative-associative merge needs no coordinator).
